On average, in winter, snow cover in the mountains of the Lesser Caucasus ranges from 10 to 30 cm. In the mountains of the Greater Caucasus (in particular, on the southwestern slope), heavy snowfalls are noted. Avalanches are a frequent occurrence from November to April. Snow cover in some regions (Svaneti , in the northern part of Abkhazia) can reach 5 meters. The Achishkho region is the snowiest place in the Caucasus, the snow cover of which reaches a depth of 7 meters.